# CharityPilot personal-server example configuration.
#
# Reference contract only. Do not copy this file into the checkout. The
# supported Windows installer creates the real .env.personal-server exclusively,
# outside the source checkout, and refuses to overwrite it:
#
#   powershell -NoLogo -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass `
#     -File .\scripts\Install-CharityPilot.ps1 -PreflightOnly
#
# The default protected state root is:
#   %LOCALAPPDATA%\CharityPilot\personal-server
# A protected personal-server-location.json pointer and the user-level
# CHARITYPILOT_PERSONAL_SERVER_ENV_FILE value locate a custom -StateRoot.
# Never commit, email or paste the generated environment, pointer, install state,
# runtime-health report, recovery key or recovery sets into an issue or chat.
#
# Install an official release only from the named CharityPilot-personal-v*.zip
# asset on the canonical GitHub Releases page, with its checksum and manifest.
# GitHub Code > Download ZIP is not an installable release bundle. The presence
# of this example does not imply that a release has been published or certified.
#
# Do not hand-edit the generated real file as a recovery procedure. Preserve an
# exact protected copy or follow the reviewed recovery/rotation runbook. Keep
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD URL-safe because Compose uses it in DATABASE_URL; a
# 64-character hexadecimal value is suitable.
# CHARITYPILOT_PERSONAL_SERVER_ORIGIN must be the exact address users open,
#    with no trailing slash. Supported values are exact loopback HTTP or this
#    host's exact default-port Tailscale .ts.net HTTPS origin. Cloudflare Tunnel,
#    Tailscale Funnel and other tunnels are unsupported.
# CHARITYPILOT_PERSONAL_SERVER_IMAGE_TAG is installer-managed: local for a
#    supervised canonical clone, or the exact personal-v* release tag.
# recovery-key.hex is a separate protected file, never an environment value.
#    It protects AES-256-GCM database/document artifacts and the manifest HMAC.
#    Installed backup fails closed rather than falling back to plaintext when
#    this key is missing. Keep its encrypted offline copy separate from copied
#    recovery sets. Losing it makes encrypted recovery sets unrestorable;
#    compromise exposes every set protected by it.

CHARITYPILOT_PERSONAL_SERVER_PORT=8080
CHARITYPILOT_PERSONAL_SERVER_ORIGIN=http://localhost:8080
CHARITYPILOT_PERSONAL_SERVER_IMAGE_TAG=local

POSTGRES_DB=charitypilot_personal_server
POSTGRES_USER=charitypilot_personal_server
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=CHANGE_ME_USE_64_HEXADECIMAL_CHARACTERS

JWT_SECRET=CHANGE_ME_JWT_USE_AT_LEAST_32_RANDOM_CHARACTERS
# Independent root secret for recovery token/rate-key derivation. Use the
# canonical even-length hex or unpadded base64url encoding of 32-64 random bytes.
# Do not reuse JWT_SECRET or READINESS_API_KEY.
AUTH_RECOVERY_SECRET=CHANGE_ME_CANONICAL_32_TO_64_RANDOM_BYTES_HEX_OR_BASE64URL
JWT_EXPIRY=15m
REFRESH_TOKEN_TTL_DAYS=7
READINESS_API_KEY=CHANGE_ME_READINESS_USE_AT_LEAST_32_RANDOM_CHARACTERS

# Used only by the explicit, profile-gated personal-init service. The compiled
# initializer refuses to overwrite an existing personal-server workspace.
PERSONAL_SERVER_OWNER_EMAIL=owner@example.invalid
PERSONAL_SERVER_OWNER_NAME=CharityPilot Owner
PERSONAL_SERVER_ORGANISATION_NAME=My Charity
# Intentionally blank: do not persist the bootstrap password in this file.
# The one-shot host initializer must inject it only for the init process.
PERSONAL_SERVER_OWNER_PASSWORD=

# Stripe, Resend, Supabase, public DNS/TLS, alert webhooks, and background jobs
# are intentionally absent from this personal-server profile.
